FT  10 FEB 92 / Construction Contracts: Channel Tunnel rail terminal
LANDIS &amp; GYR has won a Pounds 1m-plus contract from British Rail European
Passenger Services to install a building management system at Waterloo
International (pictured), the new rail terminal due to open in 1993 as the
London terminus for the Channel Tunnel passenger traffic.
The Landis &amp; Gyr System 2100 will monitor and control air conditioning,
including platform areas, as well as lighting, escalators and travelators.
